WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.360
We have something that's like a super basic form that most people when they are first

00:00:04.360 --> 00:00:08.720
using Shiny, they would end up creating and this is very basic and it kind of works, but

00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:11.360
we can make it a lot more better, a lot more cooler.

00:00:11.360 --> 00:00:18.700
If I take a look at an accordion like this, let me run it over here, simple accordion

00:00:18.700 --> 00:00:23.000
form would look something like this, when you can actually fill up a name, the email,

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:27.559
the phone number, you can hit submit or you can collapse it, separate it in different

00:00:27.559 --> 00:00:28.559
chunks.

00:00:28.559 --> 00:00:32.119
So in Dynamic Accordion, what we do is the same way you would do an accordion, but we

00:00:32.119 --> 00:00:36.160
end up actually maximize the usage of our accordion panel.

00:00:36.160 --> 00:00:40.080
So we can actually have icons, which says like, hey, which are the accordion panels

00:00:40.080 --> 00:00:42.200
that need attention from the user.

00:00:42.200 --> 00:00:46.320
In this case, I have an exclamation mark with like red, which says like, hey, these sections

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:47.840
are supposed to be filled up.

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:53.240
On hitting the submit button for like the person section, what I end up doing is I update

00:00:53.240 --> 00:00:59.880
the accordion panel, which the new title and the title is the information they ended

00:00:59.880 --> 00:01:00.880
up filling up.

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:04.559
Also update the icon, which is a green check mark.

00:01:04.559 --> 00:01:09.160
If you want to learn more about how to update the accordion panel, feel free to read the

00:01:09.160 --> 00:01:14.239
documentation for either the express mode or the core mode by going to the function

00:01:14.239 --> 00:01:19.360
reference documentation and find out different things you can do to update your accordion

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:22.639
panel when the user has finished filling up that section.

